President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Stewart M. De Soto as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Barry Goldwater Scholarship and Excellence in Education Foundation. Dr. De Soto is currently an Associate Professor of Physics and Astronomy at Wheaton College, where he has been since 2003. He has also served as a visiting scholar at the University of Chicago's Department of Astronomy and Astrophysics from 2011 to 2012. In addition, Dr. De Soto has experience as a member of the Technical Staff at Texas Instruments, where he was awarded a patent for the design of telecommunications integrated circuits. He has also worked as a Peace Corps volunteer in Papua New Guinea, teaching Math and English and contributing to rural community development. Dr. De Soto holds a B.S. from Wheaton College and a Ph.D. from the University of Illinois, Urbana-Champaign.